<br>
&quot;How arrogant to think you are the only Teir'Dal to know the depths of love, Genashai.  How very arrogant you are, as you stand here proclaiming you are the sole Teir'Dal to know what it is.  You've naut fallen far from the Father's tree, even if you think you have.<br>
<br>
&quot;Arrogance is bred in Neriak, as surely as is Hate.  And you, my lady, have arrogance in spades.  A true child of Neriak.  So, you think this love of a Feir'Dal has changed you?  Perhaps so.  I do naut doubt your words when you say you feel love for him.  But to use that love in this fashion...you slander it.  <br>
<br>
&quot;It has become your banner, your war cry, your shield.  'Look at me!  I'm in love!  Love I tell you!  I'm special!'  Please...<br>
<br>
&quot;The only Teir'dal to admit to the depths of love...&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn laughs. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;You are unique, Genashai, I'll give you that.  Your overlarge ego makes that truth.  It's palpable, like a large hound that follows you everywhere.  Be careful it does naut turn to sink it's teeth into your leg, eh?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The priestess stands, moving out into the light of the tavern, the black chain encasing her gleaming in the firelight.  She crosses her arms and stares at the magess.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Love does make one weak, as Shintou claims.  When you use it as you do now, at least.  Perhaps you've more to learn about this depth of emotion you think you've mastered?&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn snickers softly, and moves to the door.  She pauses in the opening, turning back to the room.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Arrogant fools often get their just desserts, my lady Genashai.  Ponder that when you're in the arms of your love.  I once thought as you do, and then my love was tested.  Sorely tested...&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn looks at Sarhea, and smiles slightly.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;In the end, my love is naut a banner to be waved, or a cry to be shouted to the heavens.  It is the warmth of a fire on a cold night, the quiet cry of passion shivering to silence on the breeze, the joy of coming home at last, and the eternal promise that I am naut alone.  I do naut need to proclaim to the world that I know love...it is enough that I have it.<br>
<br>
&quot;That is where we differ, child of Neriak.  Enjoy your days.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kerridwynn walked out of the Tavern, the door closing softly behind her.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><center><B><u>Kerridwynn Spellbender</b></u><BR><i>~*Vicar of Innoruuk*~<br>~*Mistress of the Scythe*~</i><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bharvestersofdarkness>Harvesters of Darkness</a><br>~~~~~~~~~~<BR><i>Something wicked this way comes...</i><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=208851>Garb of the Priestess</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=genashai>Genashai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/24/03 4:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: the voice from the shadows</span><hr size=1> *glaring at Kerridwynn, she turns fully to face her, eyes blazing* I never claimed i was the only one that felt love. I am saying I have no hatred mingled with what Teirdal call love for each other. I tell you Do i plan on consorting with other light bringers? Nau, I will not. For they are still enemies to others like me, and in holding fast their hands in friendship, I hold their enemies unto my own. But to one i vow to love, it is pure. It is of itself, and nothing more. I tell you this, Jalil, Nau, the love of a wood elf did not change me. I will tell you what changed me. It took my husband of a score or more years turning on me, and attacking me. It took the ripping of my heart from my chest and shreadding it to peices and then stomping on it. It took this same man's hateful words and attack on me very soul that made me recoil and examine what it was I had claimed as love and how it had become my mantra.  <br>
<br>
You stand there and accuse me of being arrogant and having an over large ego and as a youth and Matron I will confess, I did have such an ego.  I will also admit to using those around me to meet and cater to my needs. That was all I knew, it had been drilled into my head.  When I found myself without the house around me, I turned to my husband, i swallowed my pride, my upbringing and i went to him and joined his allegegance. I took up his cause. So now I have neither house, nor husband. I have only my pride, my resourcefulness, and knack for knowing how to make others happy. You dare judge me, you dare accuse me of extraordinary arrogance, I tell you, jalil, You do not know me. <br>
<br>
*glancing up to sarhea* You know my mind, sarhea, of disdain for you, caused by Shintou's action, I no longer have any. I realized long ago, you were no enemy to me, nor were you ever. Of morgrist..know that we remain friends, for the memory of the bond we shared, the loss we suffered, and the future we were denied. <br>
<br>
*she takes a drink of her mead, and turns to face the room once more* I did not mean to sound as if I were using what I have found as a banner, as some token to show around and elicit a response from you. Really, I only wanted to say, I have picked myself back up, while battered and bruised, and continue to walk my path. At my side, from now on will be a quiet wood elf who held my hand as I wept and wondered why the man I'd pledged myself to had treated me so cruely.  No longer will I care for the acceptance of my people, or make decisions based on what you feel is best for my welfare. <br>
<br>
I stand here a woman, a Teir'dal, a mage. of those three things I am certain. The rest I am sorting out as I come to it.  <p><br>
