Once, i cared what you thought, what you said. I believed the drivel you spill. I'm no lightbringer, I&quot;m no evil dark elf. If the truth of it should be said, then I'm a neutral. I stand in that gray area between both worlds, and have for so long searched for a way to fit in. To find a place that i belonged.  There is no truth in his softening my heart, for by your own words, it was far too soft long ago.  <br>
<br>
*she takes a deep breath, trying to steady the anger you see burning in her eyes* I think perhaps i should change my earlier statement, that i no longer had any hate inside me. For now, as I look at you standing here condemning me, sentancing me to die and predicting my end, I say before all of you here, I do hate. I hate you Shintou Shinai. I hope every duel you enter, your spells fail, your weapon breaks. I hope your pet turns on you and gouges out your beady ugly little eyes. I lay on your head this curse, May you never know another day of contentment, comfort or pleasure. May you ever be the laughing stock you allready are.  Be proud of yourself, for you have proved I do have some hate left in me, enough to hate you! <p><br>
