<br>
She breaks the silence , but speaks gently and with only a hint of sadness and none of anger.<br>
<br>
&quot;I was  foolish  Gio.  I did not listen to my head when it told me that the druid's passion for me had faded. Rather I heard his words that I was an unreasonably jealous woman, whose fears were unfounded that his sweet words were not for my ears alone.<br>
Yet how strange it is that now knowing the truth I am able to put him from my mind as unworthy of my tears&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There will now be a new Lord at our table, a sharp blade to assist my battles and a love to lift my soul, remove my loneliness and fill my heart with renewed passion.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Perhaps now Gio, I shall find that contentment of mind and satisfaction of body, the belief in the obtainment of which, has been the reason I have been able to carry on, despite so many disappointments and mistakes.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turns her head from Gio's and looks towards the opened door where stands the figure of a strong Teir 'Dal Shadow Knight and her face blossoms with radience. His eyes burn into hers sending messages of desire and love stronger then she has known for many years.<br>
<br>
She rises from the stool and as he takes her hand in his and gently kisses her fingers, she beams a smile at him then turns to introduce him to Giovannii.<br>
<br>
&quot; It is time my Lord, for you to meet my adopted son, Giovannii Armourax, blood son of my first husband and only recently the discoverer of his Lineage&quot;<br>
<br>
